{"id": "28072", "post": "<div class=\"post-28072 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-cloud tag-microsoft tag-microsoft-365 tag-office tag-office-365\" id=\"post-28072\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/microsoft-raising-fees-for-office-365/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Microsoft Raising Fees for Office 365</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/cloud/\" rel=\"tag\">cloud</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/microsoft/\" rel=\"tag\">microsoft</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/microsoft-365/\" rel=\"tag\">microsoft 365</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/office/\" rel=\"tag\">office</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/office-365/\" rel=\"tag\">office 365</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> August 20, 2021 @ 11:30 am, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/office365.png\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-28073 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/office365.png\" alt=\"Office365\" width=\"300\" height=\"182\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-was-processed=\"true\">Microsoft <a href=\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/blog/2021/08/19/new-pricing-for-microsoft-365/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"Microsoft Press Release\">announced that they are raising prices</a> for Office 365 subscriptions.</p><p>The price increase is between 10% and 16%, depending on product.&nbsp; This is the first price increase since Office 365 launched in 2011.</p><p class=\"\">On March 1, 2022, we will update our list pricing for the following commercial products:</p><table><thead><tr><td><b>Product</b></td><td><b>Old Monthly Price</b></td><td><b>New Monthly Price</b></td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Microsoft 365 Business Basic</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$6</td></tr><tr><td>Microsoft 365 Business Premium</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$20</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$22</td></tr><tr><td>Office 365 E1</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$8</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$10</td></tr><tr><td>Office 365 E3</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$20</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$23</td></tr><tr><td>Office 365 E5</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$35</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$38</td></tr><tr><td>Microsoft 365 E3</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$32</td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">$36</td></tr></tbody></table><p>According to the article, \u201cThese increases will apply globally with local market adjustments for certain regions. There are no changes to pricing for education and consumer products at this time.\u201d</p><p>All of these pricing changes will be effective March 1, 2022.</p><p>Microsoft (NYSE: <a href=\"https://www.nyse.com/quote/XNGS:MSFT\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"NYSE\">MSFT</a>) stock was <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/3732710-microsoft-stock-rises-2-after-office-price-hike-analysts-see-revenues-juiced\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"SeekingAlpha\">up on expected improved revenues</a>.</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/spamhaus-botnet-report-highli